Since you are all retards, I’ll help.

“ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: 7993”

Means that an Array is being called, array[7993] to be specific, when the array doesn’t go that high. It’ll be the server wanting something from the client that doesn’t exist. Unless you want to go trapsing through the client to find the right array, and fuck up more things, just stfu and restart the client.
[/quote]
